The problem with this is that it doesn't automatically strip whitespace. e.g. `request.POST['name'] = '   something\n  '`.

Here's a piece code that has worked very well for me for many years:

``` python
class _BaseForm(object):
    def clean(self):
        cleaned_data = super(_BaseForm, self).clean()
        for field in cleaned_data:
            if isinstance(cleaned_data[field], basestring):
                cleaned_data[field] = \
                  cleaned_data[field].replace('\r\n','\n')\
                    .replace(u'\u2018',"'").replace(u'\u2019',"'").strip()

        return cleaned_data


class BaseModelForm(_BaseForm, forms.ModelForm):
    pass
```

